In [[hydropower]], a '''surge chamber''' is a large pressurized underground chamber creating a free surface in the waterway to improve the dynamic abilities of the power plant waterways. It is generally used for long waterways when a surge shaft can not be created to fulfill the same purpose <ref>{{cite journal|url=https://brage.bibsys.no/xmlui/handle/11250/2350124|title=Svingekammer eller luftputekammere i vannkraftverk|first=Røse, Torunn|last=Engen|date=16 March 2018|publisher=}}</ref>.
