{{Infobox dam | name = Çetin Dam | name_official = | image = | image_size = | image_caption = | image_alt = | location_map = Turkey | location_map_size = | location_map_caption = | coordinates = {{coord|37|58|18|N|42|20|10|E|type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | country = Turkey | location = | purpose = Power | status =UC | construction_began = December 2011 | opening = unknown | demolished = | cost = US$678 million | owner = | dam_type = Asphalt-Concrete Core Rock-Fill Dam | dam_height = {{Convert|145|m|ft|0|abbr=on}} | dam_height_thalweg = | dam_height_foundation= | dam_length = | dam_width_crest = | dam_width_base = | dam_volume = | dam_elevation_crest = | dam_crosses = [[Botan River]] | spillway_count = | spillway_type = | spillway_capacity = | res_name = | res_capacity_total = | res_capacity_active = | res_capacity_inactive= | res_catchment = | res_surface = {{Convert|10|km2|mi2|0|abbr=on}} | res_elevation = | res_max_depth = | res_max_length ={{Convert|20|km|mi|0|abbr=on}} | res_max_width = | plant_hydraulic_head = {{Convert|140|m|ft|0|abbr=on}} | res_tidal_range = | plant_operator = | plant_commission = unknown | plant_decommission = | plant_type = | plant_turbines = 3 x 135 [[megawatt|MW]] [[Francis-type]] | plant_capacity = 405 MW<ref>{{cite web|title=Hydro News|url=http://atl.g.andritz.com/c/com2011/00/02/22/22299/1/1/0/64108727/hy-customermagazine-hn21_en.pdf|publisher=Andritz|accessdate=19 October 2012|pages=9|year=2012}}</ref> | plant_annual_gen = 1100 GWh (est.) | website = | extra = }} The '''Çetin Dam''' is a [[rock-fill dam]] with an asphalt-concrete core, currently being constructed on the [[Botan River]] in [[Siirt Province]], [[Turkey]]. The dam will be located directly downstream of the Botan and Büyük River confluence and have a height of {{Convert|145|m|ft|0|abbr=on}}. The primary purpose of the dam is [[hydroelectric]] power generation. The dam's power plant will house three 135 MW [[Francis turbine]]-generators. Also part of the Çetin project is a smaller dam {{Convert|6|km|mi|0|abbr=on}} downstream with {{Convert|45|m|ft|0|abbr=on}} in height. The Çetin lower dam will regulate outflows from the Çetin main dam and also produce hydroelectric power with a 112 MW capacity via two 56 MW [[Kaplan turbine]]-generators.
The owner was the Norwegian, [[Statkraft]], at a cost of US $678 million. The Contractor was Yϋksel-iLci Joint Venture. Veidekke Industri AS was the subcontractor for Cetin dam. Of the six dams to be built on the Botan River, it will have the largest power plant. Construction on the main dam began in December 2011 and the power plant was expected to be complete in 2015. <ref>{{cite web|title=Çetin Hydropower Project|url=http://www.statkraft.com/Images/Faktaark%20Cetin%20ENG%2020120104%20final_tcm9-18726.pdf|publisher=Statkraft|accessdate=19 October 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Norway's Statkraft to build 517-MW Cetin in Turkey|url=http://www.hydroworld.com/articles/2011/09/norways-statkraft-to-build-517-mw-cetin-in-turkey.html|accessdate=19 October 2012|newspaper=Hydro World|date=28 September 2011}}</ref> The project has experienced delays due to [[Kurdistan Workers' Party]] attacks on the construction site and equipment. In February 2016, Statkraft suspended construction.<ref>{{cite news|title=Norway's Statkraft in the HES 'Cetin arrived|url=http://www.gazetevatan.com/norvecli-statkraft-a-bu-hes-cetin-geldi-911907-ekonomi/|accessdate=24 February 2016|agency=Vatan|date=5 February 2016|language=Turkish}}</ref> The type is changed. More information will be added. ==See also== {{stack|{{Portal|Turkey|Water|Renewable energy}}}} *[[Alkumru Dam]] – downstream, completed in 2011
